    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c6c41762_e711ffc1",
        "filename": "golden/modules/dots-sk/dots-sk.js",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 151,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-26T21:21:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please define a constant MISSING_DOT in constants.js, then rewrite this as:\n\n  const firstNonMissingDot \u003d trace.data.findIndex(dot \u003d\u003e dot !\u003d\u003d MISSING_DOT);\n  const lastNonMissingDot \u003d trace.data.slice().reverse().findIndex(dot \u003d\u003e dot !\u003d\u003d MISSING_DOT);\n\nRationale: less error prone, more concise, better readability.\n\nNotes:\n- I\u0027m using \"Dot\" instead of \"Point\" in the constant names for consistency with the rest of the code.\n- slice() and reverse() make a copy and reverse items in-place, respectively. Still linear, though slightly slower. Probably still plenty fast, as array length is small. \n- I wish we had a findLastIndex function. We could add that function to the Array prototype if we really wanted to (out of scope, probably overkill for now).\n\nUseful links:\n- Array.slice: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/slice\n- Array.reverse: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/reverse\n- Array.findIndex: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/findIndex",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 136,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 151,
        "endChar": 7
      },
      "revId": "e03c144c644c768db8df7bc2dc26e43236f67b19",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "90e542f8_89eb0325",
        "filename": "golden/modules/dots-sk/dots-sk.js",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 151,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-27T17:15:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The solution for firstNonMissingDot I like. The lastNonMissingDot would require a step to re-reverse the index, so it\u0027s less clean. Coupled with the added cost of copying hundreds of integers and then reversing them (for each trace), I think it\u0027s worth hand-writing the loop.",
      "parentUuid": "c6c41762_e711ffc1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 136,
        "startChar": 0,
